The paper discusses the training dynamics of GANs and proposes a new perspective on understanding mode collapse. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new gradient penalty scheme to improve GAN training, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and game theory (cs.GT).
